<h2>Our Commitment</h2>
<p>Ament Law Group, P.C. embraces technology that enhances the quality and efficiency of our legal services while maintaining the professional judgment, competence, and confidentiality obligations that Pennsylvania's Rules of Professional Conduct require. This policy explains how we use artificial intelligence ("AI") in our practice and on this website.</p>

<h2>Use of AI in Legal Services</h2>
<p>Our attorneys may use AI tools to assist with legal research, document drafting, document review, and other tasks in connection with providing legal services. When we use AI in this capacity:</p>
<p><strong>Professional oversight.</strong> All AI-assisted work product is reviewed by a licensed Pennsylvania attorney before it is relied upon or delivered to a client. AI does not make legal decisions for our firm — our attorneys do.</p>
<p><strong>Accuracy and competence.</strong> We do not rely on AI output without independent verification. Consistent with our obligations under Pennsylvania Rule of Professional Conduct 1.1 (Competence), our attorneys review AI-assisted work for accuracy, completeness, and applicability to the specific matter.</p>
<p><strong>Confidentiality.</strong> We take reasonable measures to protect client confidentiality when using AI, consistent with our obligations under Pennsylvania Rule of Professional Conduct 1.6. We do not input client-identifying information into public or open-source AI systems without appropriate safeguards. Our practice management tools that incorporate AI functionality operate in secure, access-controlled environments.</p>
<p><strong>Transparency.</strong> Upon request, we will disclose which tasks or work product involved the use of AI tools. If we identify any material errors in AI-assisted output that may affect the legal services provided, we will promptly notify the affected client.</p>
<p><strong>Billing.</strong> Our flat-fee pricing model means that our use of AI tools to increase efficiency benefits our clients directly. We do not charge clients for AI tool costs separately, and the use of AI to streamline a task does not increase our fees.</p>

<h2>AI Chat Assistant on This Website</h2>
<p>This website features an AI-powered chat assistant that can answer general questions about our practice areas, firm services, and Pennsylvania law topics. Important limitations of the chat assistant:</p>
<p><strong>Not legal advice.</strong> The chat assistant provides general information only. It does not provide legal advice, and its responses should not be relied upon as a substitute for consultation with a licensed attorney.</p>
<p><strong>No attorney-client relationship.</strong> Interacting with the chat assistant does not create an attorney-client relationship. An attorney-client relationship with Ament Law Group is established only through a signed engagement letter.</p>
<p><strong>Not a substitute for professional counsel.</strong> The chat assistant cannot evaluate your specific legal situation. If you need legal guidance, we encourage you to <a href="/contact/">schedule a consultation</a> with one of our attorneys.</p>
<p><strong>Privacy.</strong> If you provide personal information through the chat assistant (such as your name or contact information through the lead capture form), that information is transmitted to our firm for the purpose of following up on your inquiry. We do not sell or share this information with third parties. For full details, see our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

<h2>Our Position on AI-Generated Legal Documents</h2>
<p>We have seen an increase in clients and prospective clients using AI tools and online services to generate legal documents — wills, powers of attorney, operating agreements, contracts, and other instruments. While these tools can produce documents that appear professional, they carry significant risks that we believe every consumer should understand.</p>
<p>AI tools and online document services cannot evaluate your specific legal situation, account for how Pennsylvania law applies to your particular facts, or anticipate the ways a document may fail when tested in practice. These services universally disclaim that they are not law firms and do not provide legal advice. We encourage anyone considering these tools to read our practice area pages, which address these risks in detail for each area of law we handle.</p>

<h2>Updates to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, available technology, or applicable ethical rules. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.</p>

<h2>Questions</h2>
<p>If you have questions about our use of AI or this policy, please contact us at <a href="tel:724-733-3500">(724) 733-3500</a> or through our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>

